      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:2:1:131:11",
      "text": [
        " قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ( صلى الله عليه وآله ) إِنَّ اللَّهَ يُبْغِضُ الْفَاحِشَ الْبَذِي‏ءَ وَ السَّائِلَ الْمُلْحِفَ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "From him, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Ali Bin Al Numan, from Amro Bin Shimr, from Jabir, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Ja’far<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Rasool-Allah<sup>saww</sup> said: ‘Allah<sup>azwj</sup> Hates the immoral one, the obscene one, and the insistent beggar’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "11. It is narrated from him (narrator of the Hadith above) from Ahmad ibn Muhammad from Ali ibn al-Nu’man from ‘Amr ibn Shimr from Jabir from abu Ja’far (a.s.) who has said the following: “The Messenger of Allah has said, ‘Allah hates those who use foul language and the insistant beggar.” "
        ]
      }
